BFN 

  [Text] Telephone calls were held this evening between 
Presidential Council Chairman Lieutenant General 'Ali 'Abdallah 
Salih and his brothers Shaykh Zayid Bin-Sultan Al Nuhayyan, 
president of the United Arab Emirates [UAE], and President Hafiz 
al-Asad of the Syrian Arab Republic. 
  During the two telephone conversations, the brother 
president 
informed the two leaders of the situation in our country. He 
also briefed them on the issues raised with Lakhdar Brahimi, 
envoy of the UN secretary general, in compliance with UN 
Security Council Resolution 924, which concerns the situation in 
our country. 

